examples.en: The house erupted into a fireball.
The volcano last erupted 25 years ago.
The bar erupted into gales of laughter.
The volcano erupted with tremendous force.
The audience erupted in gales of laughter.
A political row erupted over the MP's comments.
A donnybrook has erupted over the court's decision.
A bitter dispute has erupted among the members of the team.
A brouhaha erupted over her statements about the president.
A rash erupted on her arms after she had touched the exotic plant.
Extinct volcanoes are those that have not erupted in historic times.
Violence erupted after police shot a student during the demonstration.
An ethnic conflict that was simmering away in the background finally erupted into civil war.
Even after the formal surrender, spastic violence erupted in scattered quarters of the city.
When marchers gathered on a third day of protest, violence erupted and buildings were burned.
